{
  "stem": "8842.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And so she put on an unbelievable effort to bring him back home because he was very, very sick.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Actually what he had was pneumonia.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they let him come home.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So we had finally our family is back together.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And my father told us what really happened to all the men when they were also separated from us and also taken to Seventh Fort.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They were all laying in a ditch, in a big, but very large ditch, because there were thousands of men there together.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The fort was, like, built all around.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The Germans and Lithuanians were standing all around and the men were laying outside.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They were not given little barracks like we did.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They were just laying outside.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Hundreds were taken out from there to do some work, and they never came back.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Some of them, they were left.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "About 6, 7 o'clock in the evening, the Germans used to scream, 'Lay down.' So whoever wherever stood had to lay down immediately.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "If you moved a hand or a leg, if you fell on somebody and it wasn't comfortable or whatever, the Germans and Lithuanians noticed that, and they used to fire direct into that person that moved.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "That means if he was injured or he was dead, he was laying there among the live ones for seven consecutive days.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "At the end, when they decided that they are going to clean this place out, the women and the men, what they did to the men was every dead person, or not completely dead-- four men had to take that person, go up on the hill, throw him behind the other side of the hill, and these four would stand in front of the German or Lithuanian, whoever was there.",
      "word_count": 70
    }
  ],
